CAMERA CONTROLS (crates/scriptbots-render/src/lib.rs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CameraState Structure:
```rust
struct CameraState {
    offset_px: (f32, f32),     // Pan offset in screen pixels
    zoom: f32,                 // Zoom level [MIN_ZOOM, MAX_ZOOM]
    panning: bool,             // Is user currently panning?
    pan_anchor: Option<Point<Pixels>>,  // Drag start position
}

impl CameraState {
    const MIN_ZOOM: f32 = 0.4;   // Zoom out (see more world)
    const MAX_ZOOM: f32 = 2.5;   // Zoom in (see less, bigger)
    const DEFAULT_ZOOM: f32 = 1.0;
}
```

Pan Implementation:
```rust
fn start_pan(&mut self, cursor: Point<Pixels>) {
    self.panning = true;
    self.pan_anchor = Some(cursor);
}

fn update_pan(&mut self, cursor: Point<Pixels>) -> bool {
    if !self.panning { return false; }

    if let Some(anchor) = self.pan_anchor {
        let dx = f32::from(cursor.x) - f32::from(anchor.x);
        let dy = f32::from(cursor.y) - f32::from(anchor.y);

        if dx.abs() > f32::EPSILON || dy.abs() > f32::EPSILON {
            self.offset_px.0 += dx;
            self.offset_px.1 += dy;
            self.pan_anchor = Some(cursor);  // Update anchor for next delta
            return true;  // Request repaint
        }
    }
    false
}

fn end_pan(&mut self) {
    self.panning = false;
    self.pan_anchor = None;
}
```

Pan behavior:
- Drag with mouse to pan view
- Accumulates delta from anchor point
- Updates anchor each frame (smooth continuous panning)
- Returns true when view changed (triggers repaint)

Zoom Implementation:
```rust
fn apply_scroll(&mut self, event: &ScrollWheelEvent) -> bool {
    let scroll_y = match event.delta {
        ScrollDelta::Pixels(delta) => -f32::from(delta.y) / 120.0,
        ScrollDelta::Lines(lines) => -lines.y,
    };

    if scroll_y.abs() < 0.01 { return false; }

    let old_zoom = self.zoom;
    self.zoom = (self.zoom * (1.0 + scroll_y * 0.1))
        .clamp(MIN_ZOOM, MAX_ZOOM);

    // Scale pan offset to maintain view center
    let ratio = self.zoom / old_zoom;
    self.offset_px.0 *= ratio;
    self.offset_px.1 *= ratio;

    true  // Request repaint
}
```

Zoom behavior:
- Scroll wheel controls zoom (10% per line)
- Clamped to [0.4, 2.5] range (prevents excessive zoom)
- Pan offset scaled proportionally (maintains apparent center point)
- Supports both pixel deltas (trackpad) and line deltas (mouse wheel)

